int y = 0;
if (y != 0) {
    int z = x / y;
    // Use z here
} else {
    // Handle the case where y is zero
    // For example, you could throw an exception or print an error message
    printf("Error: Division by zero!\n");
}
```

Alternatively, you could also use a try-catch block to catch the ArithmeticException that is thrown when attempting to divide by zero:

```c
int x = 5;
int y = 0;
try {
    int z = x / y;
    // Use z here
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    // Handle the exception
    printf("Error: Division by zero!\n");
}
```

